quran[28]{c,v,t}:
  74,48,"So the intercession of the intercessors will not benefit them. (The disbelievers will not have any intercessor.)"
  74,49,"So what is the matter with them that they turn away from the advice?"
  74,50,"As if they were startled donkeys –"
  74,51,"Fleeing away from a lion."
  74,52,"Rather each one of them desires that he should be given open Books."
  74,53,"Never! In fact they do not fear the Hereafter."
  74,54,"Yes indeed, this is an advice."
  74,55,"So whoever wills may heed advice from it."
  74,56,"And what advice will they heed, except if Allah wills? Only He deserves to be feared, and His only is the greatness of forgiving."
  75,1,"I swear by the Day of Resurrection."
  75,2,"And by oath of the soul that reproaches itself."
  75,3,"Does man assume that We will never assemble his bones?"
  75,4,"Surely yes, why not? We can properly make all his phalanxes."
  75,5,"In fact man wishes to commit evil in front of Him!"
  75,6,"He asks, “When will be the Day of Resurrection?”"
  75,7,"So when the eyes will be blinded by light."
  75,8,"And the moon will be eclipsed."
  75,9,"And the sun and the moon will be united."
  75,10,"On that day man will cry out, “Where shall I flee?”"
  75,11,"Never! There is no refuge!"
  75,12,"On that day, the station is only towards your Lord."
  75,13,"On that day, man will be informed of all what he sent ahead and left behind."
  75,14,"In fact, man himself is keeping an eye on his state of affairs!"
  75,15,"And even if he presents all the excuses he has, none will be listened to."
  75,16,"O dear Prophet (Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him), do not cause your tongue to move along with the Qur’an in order to learn it faster."
  75,17,"Indeed assembling the Qur’an and reading it are upon Us."
  75,18,"So when We have read it, you should thereupon follow what is read."
  75,19,"Then indeed, to explain its details to you is upon Us."
